# RD29A Drought Stress Gene Analysis

I built this pipeline to explore the molecular biology 
behind plant drought tolerance — something I find 
genuinely fascinating given my background in 
environmental biotechnology.

## What this project does

Starting from the RD29A gene sequence in Arabidopsis 
thaliana, this notebook walks through:

- Fetching the gene directly from NCBI
- Analyzing nucleotide composition and GC content
- Designing PCR primers for marker-assisted breeding
- Translating the sequence into protein
- Visualizing the protein structure in 3D

## Why RD29A?

RD29A is one of the most studied stress-response genes 
in plants. Understanding how it works at the sequence 
level is a first step toward engineering drought-tolerant 
crops — which matters a lot in water-scarce regions 
like the Middle East.

## Tools used

Python, Biopython, py3Dmol, Google Colab, NCBI Entrez

